& [LambdaOscilloscopeProbeSpecification] is the local authority for this tool implementation
  + [specification_uuid] is 33581a78-b859-46a3-927c-372f9adbfa1b
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [tool_helper] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\rh_math\lambda_oscilloscope.py
  + [tool_script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\lambda_oscilloscope_probe.py
  + [purpose] is emit finite Lambda log-Fourier phasor traces and optional term rows for deterministic inspection
  + [proof_status] is finite_lambda_oscilloscope_trace_not_rh_evidence

& [FiniteTraceFormula] is the implemented mathematical object
  + [series] is E_{sigma,N,W}(t) = sum over prime powers q <= N of Lambda(q) * W_N(q) * q^(-sigma) * exp(-i*t*log(q))
  + [lambda_rule] is Lambda(p^k) = log(p) for prime p and integer k >= 1
  + [hard_window] is W_N(q) = 1
  + [fejer_window] is W_N(q) = max(0, 1 - q/(N + 1))
  + [trace_row] is sigma, t, prime_power_bound, window, term_count, value, magnitude, and optional comparison residual
  + [term_row] is sigma, t, prime, exponent, prime_power, Lambda weight, window weight, amplitude, phase, and contribution

  = must: use natural logarithm
  = must: sort term rows by prime_power, prime, exponent
  = must: include prime powers, not only primes
  = must: reject nonpositive prime_power_bound
  = must: reject sigma < 0
  = must: reject negative t values for default trace generation
  = must: cap sample count to avoid accidental huge traces

& [ConvergenceBoundary] is the comparison contract
  + [sigma_greater_than_one] is eligible for comparison to -zeta_prime(s)/zeta(s)
  + [sigma_less_or_equal_one] is finite trace only and not compared to the infinite Lambda Dirichlet series
  + [comparison_residual] is finite_trace minus exact -zeta_prime(s)/zeta(s) when sigma > 1 and comparison is enabled

  = must: label comparison availability in payload rows
  = must: omit exact comparison for sigma <= 1
  - never: present finite critical-line traces as convergent infinite series

& [ImplementationPlan] is the required implementation slice
  + [step_1] is create rh_math.lambda_oscilloscope helper with lambda_oscilloscope_probe and window_weight helpers
  + [step_2] is create tools/scripts/lambda_oscilloscope_probe.py CLI
  + [step_3] is update tools README and package export list
  + [step_4] is add focused tests for prime-power inclusion, windowing, comparison boundary, and proof status
  + [step_5] is run the Python test suite and record analysis

& [AcceptanceCriteria] is the completion standard
  + [prime_power_test] is bound 10 includes 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, and 9 as active Lambda terms
  + [hard_window_test] is every hard-window term has weight 1
  + [fejer_window_test] is q = 2 at N = 10 has weight 1 - 2/11
  + [comparison_test] is sigma = 2 includes a finite residual against -zeta_prime(s)/zeta(s)
  + [boundary_test] is sigma = 0.5 reports no infinite-series comparison
  + [proof_boundary_test] is metadata proof_status finite_lambda_oscilloscope_trace_not_rh_evidence
